reviews.name: Coffeyville Regional Medical Center
reviews.subtypes: Hospital, Anesthesiologist, Emergency care physician, Family practice physician, Hospital department, Orthopedic surgeon, Pathologist

posts.body: CRMC is proud to be the only hospital in the region to be Accredited by The Joint Commission - the oldest and most respected healthcare accreditation body in healthcare.

reviews_data.review_text: Very pleasant experience!! No wait time and the hospital was very very clean. All staff were so efficient and friendly made me feel very comfortable and safe while there I couldn’t have asked for more! The nurse and Dr. Landon Vinson were incredible one of the best doctors I’ve been to or experienced ever. Very knowledgeable and makes sure you are completely taken care of I very much appreciated it! Thank you to all staff for making the experience much better than it could’ve been. Will definitely not hesitate to come back if in need of anything they are the absolute best!!! :)
Took my mother for a swallowed ring. She was treated fine. Xrayed n all it took   less than one hour. In a big state we would of been there for a couple hours

This facility deserve NEGATIVE FIVE STAR. Worst service ever. Got charge excessively going to the ER. I did a lot of waiting around and it took 3 plus hrs for a 5min service. The Dr did not call me back for the results that I have been waiting on.

I booked an appointment ahead of time. When I showed up, they said they called me prior to cancel my appointment which I did not receive. I checked my inbound history calls and there was not a single call from them what so ever. This happened 3 times already. I’m FED UP with their services. DO NOT COME HERE. STAY AWAY and keep your money
Worst experience we've had so far, and far from the first. My elderly father went to E.R. for severe pain, was given a SLEEPING pill, and sent on his way. Pathetic.

I was treated very badly in the er was called a liar made fun of had the cops called on me because I was insisting to talk to my Dr I told them I had no feeling in my legs they made me get up and when I fell they refused to help me up and they said I fell on purpose then the nurses made fun of me falling

I would give a lower rating if it were possible. My daughter was in a serious car accident. When I arrived, she was alone in an ER room, she had a thin blanket, was still wearing her shoes. She was dirty and literally covered in leaves from crawling out of her vehicle. No one had the decency to help get leaves from her hair!! Staff was incredibly rude and wanted to be combative over my frustration instead of giving me her medical condition. I’m just amazed anyone, especially some one in health care, found it appropriate to leave a young woman in a bed covered in dirt and leaves!! I just have no words
Hospital staff very disrespectful and need to be reeducated on hospital etiquette or fired whichever comes first.
I went in to have a cyst drained. Was very impressed with the fast pace which everything happened. Everyone was so friendly and helpful.
Horrible not timely efficient at all and dont care about your well being! They just want the check.

If I could give NEGATIVE stars I certainly would. The hospital emergency room does the bare minimum for patients and their bedside manner is literally non-existent. My wife has Lupus and so gets sick very very easily. She has been there numerous times and nearly EVERY time the staff has brought her to literal tears with their inconsideration and rudeness. I even calmly voiced my displeasure to the nurse in charge one night and was firmly escorted by security from the building. Tonight it was due to complications from Corona Virus and she was treated very poorly because of her personal decision to not be vaccinated.  Vaccination is a choice and patients should NOT be treated like less than normal because of a personal choice!!! Shame on you!!!
Do not go here unless you have money because if you don't you will be sued by the hospital

My boyfriend and I are from Arkansas city and we contracted covid a couple of weeks ago. I am doing well but my boyfriend had to be flown to CRMC to the ICU to continue treatment. Before he was intubated, he raved about how nice and kind the nurses in the ICU were being to him. THANK YOU SO MUCH to all the nurses in the ICU. They have been so patient with me and I call A LOT! They are always so kind and helpful, and I am so thankful to them for taking such good care of my boyfriend while he is sick. He means the world to me, and it makes it especially hard that I can’t be there with him. I am going to have to send some gift baskets or something to show the nurses how much I appreciate them! I have never been to coffeyville myself but I wish I could, just to meet and thank every one of the nurses that have been taking such good care of Chris Austin. Thank you all so much.

Went in to er at 9 in the morning  with all the symptoms of a heart attack no one in the ER no parking in the ER parking area.  My husband finally found someone told them what was going on they didn't seem concerned at all.  A nurse finally came out asked me a few questions my daughter had to answer then she strolled away.   We went back about 15 to 20 mins after arriving.  The rest of the docs and nurse were great but no one seem in that big of a hurry with the exception of a few.  The room I was in was dirty trash under the bed and all three trash bins so full you could close the lid.  The admissions lady was just plan unpleasant.

Do not go to this hospital if you do not want to be charged for something, even if you have the best insurance in the world! They will find a loop-hole in your insurance to charge you with something, anything. Even if it's a $100 q-tip!

Horrible hospital facility. Went it 4 times for the same issue. Kept. Not listening to a word me or my wife said. Ended up going in yesterday morning and was sent home within 20 mins without even being checked out. Ended up driving to Bartlesville Oklahoma to the hospital there and with in 3 hours diagnosed me. And treated me!! this hospital is a joke. I would highly recommend going to Bartlesville or any other facility especially if your life depends on it. Then they make you sign paperwork to cover their screw ups. Be aware of this facility. Again don't go there even if you think your dying!!!

Great staff and Facilities. Lots of volunteers to help, answer questions and get you to where you need to be. Fairly easy to find as it is only a few blocks north of the main road going through town on the west side. Plenty of parking surrounds the hospital. The nurses and doctors all seem to enjoy their job.

Great Doctor's, poor time management.  Clinic appointments have averaged us a two hour wait, one hour in the waiting room and at least one hour in the room.  Nothing major besides a yearly checkup for a child and a couple shots.

The billing department is one of the best. The staff throughout each department  is professional, polite,  and helpful. If I have a question, they have always been able to answer/solve the problem immediately.

Inform the administration if you have a problem  before rating the hospital as poor. The administration works hard to solve problems and provide excellent service for the community. If the administration doesn’t know about the problem they can’t fix the problem.
Cami at the desk is always so nice and helpful. I am always glad to see her when I come in.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Isn't she the best!!!! We love her too.

reviews_data.review_text: I went to the emergency room because my shoulder came out of socket. They were very courteous and professional. They took great care of me and got me  on my way within a couple hours thanks to the doctor and the nurses that help me.
